{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f01cd191-f5eb-445c-8f8c-ce4da75e1b97","content":"For a **.NET Web API** project, use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD (organizational) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# API with Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg\n\n# API with Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` if you need custom token validation (e.g., Auth0, IdentityServer).\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` for the full list of options including `--calls-graph`, `--called-api-url`, and framework targeting.\n\nWould you like help scaffolding a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c824a964-61d1-4cce-a6c5-7972dc4c597d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/development question. Let me check if there's relevant context in the current working directory or if this is just a general knowledge question.\n\nGiven the environment context says the directory contents are unavailable and it's not a git repository, this seems like a general question. I can answer this from my knowledge about common web API templates and authentication options.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about common web API project templates (like ASP.NET Core Web API, Express.js, etc.) and their authentication options. Given the repository instructions mention .NET/NuGet, the user might be asking about .NET specifically.\n\n\nSince this appears to be a general knowledge question rather than something tied to their s